{% comment %}
  Radius Bundle - Product Card Template

  This snippet is used as a reference for the HTML structure
  that JavaScript will generate for each product.

  The actual rendering happens in JS because product data
  comes from the app database, not Shopify metafields.

  This file serves as documentation of the expected HTML structure.
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %}
  LIST LAYOUT - Product Item HTML Structure:

  <div class="radius-bundle__product radius-bundle__product--list" data-product-id="gid://...">
    <div class="radius-bundle__product-image">
      <img src="..." alt="..." loading="lazy" />
    </div>
    <div class="radius-bundle__product-info">
      <h4 class="radius-bundle__product-title">Product Title</h4>
      <div class="radius-bundle__product-variants" data-variant-selector>
        <!-- Variant selectors if applicable -->
      </div>
      <div class="radius-bundle__product-quantity">
        Qty: <span data-quantity>1</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="radius-bundle__product-price">
      <span class="radius-bundle__product-price-current">$29.99</span>
      <span class="radius-bundle__product-price-compare">$39.99</span>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endcomment %}

{% comment %}
